SIMPLE: sneck
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sneck
<hw>Sneck</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Snatch</er>.]</ety> <def>To fasten by a hatch; to latch, as a
door.</def> <mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sneck up</b></col>, <cd>be silent; shut up; hold your
peace.</cd></cs> <-- Obs or archaic? --> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sneck</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sneck
<hw>Sneck</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A door latch.</def> <mark>[Scot. &
Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sneck band</b></col>, <cd>a latchstring.</cd>
<au>Burns.</au> -- <col><b>Sneck drawer</b></col>, <cd>a latch lifter; a
bolt drawer; hence, a sly person; a cozener; a cheat; -- called also
<altname>sneckdraw</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Sneck drawing</b></col>,
<cd>lifting the latch.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snecket</ent>⟦br⟧
